## 22. T-Test Experience / t 检验经验

**English**

I have experience using t-tests to compare continuous variables between two groups in clinical trial and RWE analyses.

Examples include: age, laboratory values, change from baseline, treatment duration, length of stay, healthcare costs, quality-of-life scores, and biomarker levels.

I assess independence, approximate normality, sample size, outliers, and equality of variances.

When group variances are similar, a pooled t-test may be appropriate. When variances are unequal, I use Welch's t-test.

For paired measurements, such as baseline and post-treatment values in the same patients, I use a paired t-test if the distribution of within-patient differences is appropriate.

If assumptions are not satisfied, I consider nonparametric alternatives such as the Wilcoxon rank-sum test or Wilcoxon signed-rank test.

I report the mean difference, confidence interval, and p-value rather than only the p-value. In RWE studies, I also consider confounding and may use regression models for adjusted comparisons.

**中文**

