## 36. Final Professional Positioning / 最终职业定位

**English**

My background is well suited to an RWE Analyst role because I understand both the clinical meaning of healthcare data and the technical requirements needed to turn those data into reliable evidence.

I can work across the full analytical lifecycle:

- Clarifying the research question
- Evaluating data fitness
- Designing the observational study
- Defining cohorts and variables
- Extracting large datasets
- Programming analysis-ready data
- Applying statistical methods
- Assessing confounding and bias
- Validating results
- Communicating limitations

My clinical trial experience provides strong discipline in specifications, endpoint definitions, traceability, and quality control. My RWE experience adds expertise in claims, EHRs, registries, observational design, target trial emulation, propensity-score methods, missing data, and real-world bias.

My SAS, SQL, R, Python, Unix, cloud, and distributed-data experience allows me to work effectively across data engineering, statistical programming, and analysis tasks.

Most importantly, I do not treat RWE as only a statistical modeling exercise. I recognize that reliable evidence begins with a clearly defined question, an appropriate data source, a sound study design, transparent operational definitions, and rigorous validation. Statistical methods are then used to support—not replace—those foundations.

